<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The 90 Day Fiancé franchise is finally coming to Australia.</p>

<p>At the Channel Nine Upfronts on Wednesday, the network announced that they would be releasing 'fast-tracked episodes' of the show exclusively on the 9Now streaming service.</p>

<p>The first four seasons of the main show are already available on 9Now, but more are on the way. </p>

<p>Coming soon! Channel Nine announced that they will be releasing 'fast-tracked episodes' of 90 Day Fiancé exclusively on the 9Now streaming service beginning October. (Pictured: Darcey Silva)</p>

<p>From October 1st, 9Now will have season five of the original flagship show, along with the first seasons of Before the 90 Days and Happily Ever After.  </p>

<p>90 Day Fiancé is currently one of the most popular reality TV franchises in the world.</p>

<p>It's one of the highest rated franchises in America, allowing its network TLC to surpass Bravo (home of The Real Housewives franchise) in ratings and key demos. </p>

<p>Tune in! From October 1st, 9Now will have season five of the original flagship show, along with the first seasons of Before the 90 Days and Happily Ever After. (Pictured: Big Ed)</p>

<p>Since its launching in 2014, its spawned no less than ten spin-offs, with more to come next year.</p>

<p>The show follows couples from different countries and cultures, one American and one foreigner, in long-distance relationships. </p>

<p>It's already featured one Australian participant in Erika Owens, who also made history as one half of the first ever same-sex couple to be featured on the show.</p>

<p>Plot: The show follows couples from different countries and cultures, one American and one foreigner, in long-distance relationships. (Pictured: Angela Deem and Michael Ilesanmi)</p>

<p>Erika and her internet girlfriend Stephanie Matto starred on season five of Before the 90 Days earlier this year.</p>

<p>During their season, Stephanie left America to stay with Erika in Port Augusta to see if their online romance could work in the real world. </p>

<p>Unfortunately, the couple split shortly after filming and have since gone on to find success as influencers and OnlyFans models.</p>

<p>Down Under: Australia's own Erika Owens (right) and her internet girlfriend Stephanie Matto (left) starred on season five of Before the 90 Days earlier this year</p>
